
---------------ANGULAR CLI----------------------
The Angular CLI is a command line interface tool that can create a project, add files, and perform a variety of ongoing development tasks such as testing, bundling, and deployment.
    //https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/wiki
    //https://github.com/angular/angular-cli#documentation
    //https://cli.angular.io/
npm install -g @angular/cli
    //The Angular CLI makes it easy to create an application
    //that already works, right out of the box. It already follows our best practices!
    //The Angular CLI is a tool to initialize, develop, scaffold and maintain Angular applications

    //Create new project
$ ng new NEWPROJECTNAME
     //Redirect
$ cd NEWPROJECTNAME
    //Build before installing express
$ ng build
    //Get express
npm install express body-parser --save
---app.get VS app.use---
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15601703/difference-between-app-use-and-app-get-in-express-js
